    "name": "ConvKB",
    "description": "ConvKB is a novel embedding model proposed for knowledge base completion. It advances existing state-of-the-art models by utilizing a convolutional neural network (CNN), allowing it to capture global relationships and transitional characteristics between entities and relations. In ConvKB, every triple (head entity, relation, tail entity) is initially represented as a 3-column matrix. This matrix is fed into a convolution layer where multiple filters generate various feature maps. These feature maps are then concatenated into a single feature vector representing the input triple. Finally, this feature vector generates a score by being multiplied with a weight vector via a dot product. This score predicts whether the given triple is valid. Experiments demonstrated that ConvKB achieved superior link prediction performance compared to previous state-of-the-art models on two benchmark datasets: WN18RR and FB15k-237.",
